===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=䏒,膨-Min Nan vernacular,肨-ancient or Min Nan vernacular}}
According to STEDT, possibly from {{der|zh|sit-pro|*s-bʷam ~ s-bʷap|t=to swell; swollen, fat, thick; rounded part, mountain, hill}}. Cognates include {{och-l|墳|bulge, mound}}, possibly {{och-l|芃|luxuriant growth}}, and, outside of Sinitic, {{cog|bo|སྦོམ་|t=thick, bulky, fat}}. A more distant cognate is {{cog|my|ဝမ်း|t=belly}}.
